urned up a bit from me sisters you see and oh she was a - grey flannel dressing gown, a long one, it was in good condition. She washed it, cut it - undid all the - unpicked it, turned it inside out and pressed it and she made me the most wonderful frock I
 ever had - for Sunday. Well that was the kind of woman she was. And - down Hockley, it was still there then, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5112414\charrsid14039999 cheapest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
