 name, he said he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5112414\charrsid14039999 D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 efan. No my child, it's not his name, it's what we call him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Can you remember any of the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 And then there was another - one with a big head and his - one of his eyes used to be in the corner. Well - I got - giggling f
its, we all did, I wasn't the only one, grace as well, and my mother said, oh my goodness, he's coming across the yard again. Wed got this backyard. Dad says, I shall give you one if any of you start and laugh. Don't giggle. And he would send me to the do
o
r. And this man would look at me, I never knew whether he was looking at - me or not - great big head on a thin body. He says, is your dad in? I said, yes. I said, do you want to see him. He says, yes. He says, tell him it's poor Joe. So - pushed the midd
l
e door open, I said, dad, it's poor Joe. He sent us all - up to bed. Go on, off you go. And I had to get the explanation right, he was such a poor old thing. His name in the workshop was poor Joe. It wasn't his name, eh'd got this wandering eye, but if yo
u'd have seen the cut he made, you would never - laugh, oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did your father ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. Only on one occasion in his life - only - oh two occasions - every good fair, he took us down Saturday afternoon and let 
