i
te happily enough, we thought we'd see all there was. And the band and that. And then he'd take us to the sat all and for very few coppers he bought us all one of those little sticks of brandy snaps. It was Grace, John and I. I can remember most of, becau
se Harriet had gone to work, so of course she didn't come. And then he bought a pound of russet apples. He never ate an apple himself. But if he bought one for us we must have a russet. And - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5112414\charrsid14039999 he\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  take you there and just bring you round on the outskirts and take you back. Well we thought we were queens and everything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What was the animal thing you mentioned?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Bostock and Rumbolds. They always had a big menagerie and it - when - no - when the old Exchange was there, not as it is now, the front
age came at the bottom of - where was it - along - it was - you've seen the pictures of it, well it was always drawn up there, there was a brass on the front and there was either a couple of monkeys or a bear or something all chained up, that you - oh you
 used to stand fascinated. But it was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did he ever take you to anything simpler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 We walked round - slowly round. But it - that was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5112414\charrsid14039999 key point}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 . We loved it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did he ever take you out in between whiles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 And then - no, no
t dad. But mother took us twice with an auntie of mine - to - Wifford Roundhouse. One summer. She put some tea and - bottles and bread and butter, packed it up in sandwiches and we crossed - I'd never been across the toll bridge before. It was quite a -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 There was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5112414\charrsid14039999 toll bridge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Yes. And - it was me auntie who kidded mother on, she said, go on take 'em out, they never get out with you. Oh and it was wonderful. There was this - walked along this lane after we'd cross the bridge and - into a sort of a farmhouse yard, there }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5112414\charrsid14039999 were long trestle tables}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  and the lady - fetched - came round and asked us if we'd like hot water. If we'd got the tea with us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You were expected to take your own tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh - yes. Or anything else we wanted. Oh it was 
lovely. It was out of doors. You see, it was such an exception to anything we'd done before. And - yes - and she did take us at least once a year, in the summer. And dad took us to see the Goose Fair.
