 peace you know. 'Cos they called me the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6840067\charrsid14039999 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 atter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6840067\charrsid14039999 er}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 , I was always on about something. Natterer. Well she - we took her. In the gods. She said, oh
 my God, when she saw the stairs. Oh now she loved - was - you know, just a - turns. Nothing very serious. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6840067\charrsid14039999 laughed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 to the - but she said she never knew - she was laughing out loud in the wrong places. And Grace said, mum, you wait 'til he's done before you start to laugh. Well - and then when we came - coming home -
