\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did the Band of Hope do anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes., We used to be - have a - a big sort of concert once a year and each little Band of Hope from the mission sen
t to - all of them from Nottingham went to the Albert - the Albert - no, Circus Street Hall. Circus Street Hall it then was. And - there would sing, for prizes you see and recite and - give - readings and all that kind of thing. We really looked forward t
o it, it was a red letter day and it was a great honour for the mission if you won anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you win anything ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What did you win?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 First prize for recitation. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Could you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14505167\charrsid14039999 do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  it still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. Yes. Yes. I've forgo
t the title but - a schoolboy at school once more sedate than the rest, had once his integrity put to the test. I can't follow it all up but I - I know how it starts. And I always remember why they gave me the prize. I couldn't understand it. 'Cos I said 
i
t wasn't really interesting, I didn't want to have it but it was a set piece. And I had to do it. And - but judges said it was - you said it was for the clearest - he meant I told the tale straightforwardly and he said you could follow every word. And the
y gave me the first prize. I had to stand up at the mission and they all clapped when we got back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Was grace said in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No, only privately to yourself. Mother would always say, goodnight, God bless you. And don't forget to say your prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did anyone teach you how to say prayers when you were little, did he older children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. We sort of followed on after them. We copied the older ones all the time you see. What you didn
't know you copied them. And of course the Captain who we got to - oh we were went there for years, he sued to say - now even if you don't say them out loud you just kneel down and say them. And we thought we was doing something clever because we were ple
asing him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Well we always used to say he was a Conservative but - he never took any personal interest. He'd read the paper and talk about it as men do. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14505167\charrsid14039999 But I never knew him take any personal interest
 in - he would - when he worked for his craft for his father, there was a trade - trades council, a very crude affair from what I could; gather and what I can remember - but - the president of this trades council, I always remember his name was Mr }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987527\charrsid14039999 Thornilow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14505167\charrsid14039999 , and - used to take dad with him. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
He said, you can't write, pop, but you can speak, so he had - he liked to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15204605\charrsid14039999 take}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 him for the men - the workmen's point of view in this trades council and dad looked forward very much to that, it only happened perhaps once in three months. But he took no - personal - affair - interest in the affairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did your mother have any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. She thought it was a waste of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Do you remember of them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14505167\charrsid14039999 voting in a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes. They -
 oh father thought it was a crime not to - even - I once heard him saying to another man - men's died to get you that vote. The least you can do is to go and use it. Oh - they always went to vote. If they were well enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 In some places at that time 
men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well - I don't think so. I never heard of anythin
g like that - at all. There weren't - houses that belonged to a firm, you know, it was sort of got a hold on them they were just ordinary - landlord held houses that - unless you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14505167\charrsid14039999 misbehaved}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  yourself or didn't pay your rent there was no fear of you losing the house. As far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 So your parents voted but they didn't take any part in political parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. Oh no. They thought that was their share I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Well they did - the one luxury was the Post of the evening and these two Sunday books of - when I'd - we'd helped them, you'd taught them to read, they used to read. But they didn't do anything else. And talk. Some - sometimes mum and dad would talk
, and sometimes they'd tell us bits about the old - things when they were children. Especially if we'd been naughty. And mother said, and when I was such and such an age I was working and doing this and doing that. And she must have been only about a chil
d eight years old. You see. And father said - I can't remember when I didn't work. And it wasn't a - he didn't say it as a - got a grudge against it for it, it was just - everybody else did the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Your mother didn't have any interests outside the home at all did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
No. She never - I used to say to her - the Captain says, do you want to come the Bright Hour or something once a week mother? He would like to meet you. And he hadn't time to go and visit everybody. So she said, I've got no time, 
I've got my work to do. You see, she - every spare minute she was at the chebonning, because it was her livelihood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When he was - of course he was working in - at grand - at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14505167\charrsid14039999 granddad
\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  whi
le he was - often late, eight o'clockish. But when he - it finished and he had got this job at the Mangus Street factory - sort of odd job man and that, his hours were from six in the morning 'til six at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh he never went out. Very - just - just for the - about once in - periodically, it didn't come regularly every week. And I can't - odd times of one of the men who he worked with in grandad's shop, they used to come and have a chat with him.
 But he never - didn't go out much himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did he ever attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
No, because we - they - they did have a pint and a half of beer every night for their supper. And - as you grow old enough to go to the pub and fetch it for them, that was one tumbler and a half each. And it was their only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14505167\charrsid14039999 indulgence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 . And - and a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14505167\charrsid14039999 slice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  of dry bread and a bit of cheese, that's all they ever had. He'd go with - if any of boys - suppose there was a party or a wedding or something coming off, and one of
 them'd say, come on dad, put your coat on, come on we'll go and have a drink. Well he might go then. But he didn't make a practice of it. He wanted it - he loved it at home. What little he had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 And your mother en}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10768088\charrsid14039999 j}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 oyed it too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh she did. She looked forward to it. Very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 She wouldn't go out to a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did women go to pubs or were they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10768088\charrsid14039999 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  pubs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Very much men's pubs. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You told me about the boot club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did they belong to any other sayings clubs?
