Yes, I believe she did have one - from - some - I don't know where he came from, this man used to call every Saturday for money and she said it was a cheque for clothing. Such as wh
en she wanted replacements and - things that she - she couldn't buy. But we had to come to some shop, I always remember it was all way up Bradford. She once took me with her. It was only - not a very big shop at all but she - was in that for years, while 
I was small, I don't know whether she - I don't think she kept it on
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Were they in a sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10768088\charrsid14039999 Oh the - ordinary insurance for death, everybody - when you got married we all said the first thing to do you must ge
t insured, penny - threepence for the father, tuppence for the mother and a penny for any subsequent children. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
And each - each year - I was living at home you see when I got - and she said, you must remember and get that insurance, you'll manage to pay tha
t much, and no more, it's - it's a drain on you. And of course it would have been. And she'd got all these - we used to laugh about them, penny policies. But nothing else, no other preparation was made. As far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh - very well, really, on the whole. But we did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16141294\charrsid14039999 argue}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  a lot to each other and we were very jealous of each other. You know, if little - if we thought that mother was - or father was showing the slightest more interest in one tha
n another, we'd say, him. you know, and we'd be really huffy about it. But - I don't think we were an antagonistic family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. Harriet. When I was so ill, I always had this reached bronchitis and we
 lived in this little house and - I had to go - I had - they used to lay me on the sofa in blankets and then mother would say, I'm getting tired, you carry her up to bed Harriet in a blanket. And she - I held on to her hand tight, could you just sing me o
n
e little song? And she - very good because she wanted to go out because she was a big girl then you see 'cos - she was about six years older than me I think in any case. And I loved her because she never grumbled. And she'd always sing a song to me. I cou
ld almost sing through half of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 As a child who did you place with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Mostly Grace and John. With two next - Grace was two years older than I and John was two years younger. But anybody round about, we sort of played in groups, we had a big sk
ipping rope, we stretched out across the big wide - road we lived in and used - oh we loved that in - we played stick and goose, have you heard of that before. Oh. Oh yes. Mother - stick - just an ordinary stick and a goose was goose. It was a little bit 
of wood and I - we used to have to get dad or Albert to sharpen the ends and you laid it on the floor and the end stood up and you used to say one, two, three, and hit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16141294\charrsid14039999 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  end. And it spun it up into the air and they used to measure how far each of you could get it. The farther you got the goose - as we called it, you - you was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15204605\charrsid14039999 winning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  the game. And we all stood in line and took it in turns to do this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How long would a goose have been, about four inches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, four or five. Oh not very tick. Just s
o that it was side enough to go with a tap on this - on this - but it had got to be pointed you see because otherwise you - it would have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16141294\charrsid14039999 stuck}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  to the floor but you see it was just that bit off where the pointed end came. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16141294\charrsid14039999 We all - and we - and we - pancake
 Tuesday as we called it, there used to be little barber on a shop and used to make us little wooden battle dores and tiny little wooden shillycocks we called them, and whips and tops for the boys, it were only - she'd save ever so - ha'penny at a time to
 give us - they were only about a penny each. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh - we loved them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15204605\charrsid14039999 these}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
