ile were' at work. So this lady was speaking to us about it, she was from the Red Cross I believe, she said, well you can go in the evenings. And - do you know where Eastcroft is? Or do you - have you heard of it? Well - on London Road. Yes. Well it's rig
h
t down the London Road and I was right up this end of the town so me sister Grace and I, so I said, we'll go, it's lark. Come up and - you know, when you think of it seriously. And we had to go two nights a week for two hours and - we had to study, you kn
ow, first - we took first aid first and then we - doctors examined us and what we'd done and then after that we had a period of a fortnights rest and then we went again.
