So she says, well I've never been used to eating - she was so different to us, she didn't eat a - a - I said, did you leave any? So she says, I have to eat it else Joyce doesn't seem to be very pleased with me, you see. And she says, you know you've not b
r
ought her up very well Annie. I said, haven't I? She said, no. and I was getting me blood up. I said, well you only had one did you not Jemima. I says, I've had four. I said, and I can't and a cantankerous man as well so, I said, I don't - think I've done
