n. Our Alice was generous. Julie wasn't. We called Julie the mean one, but Alice - and I would often give me sweets, she was a terror for that. I used to say, can you buy those sweets. Yes, she says, and I can always spare you one. And Alice did too, Alic
e never failed with - if she'd had some - they never gave you the money to go and buy them, but if they'd had some there was always so many left in the bag - few sweets for you.
