\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When you started work did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well we used to dodge if we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What did you dodge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you go to church just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 We did - we'd go in the morning. We didn't object to that, we got out of things doing at home by going. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12987527\charrsid14039999 But we - we went - to Sunday school in the afternoon, and if it was a lovely day - come on, lets go down the embankment. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh we loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you take any interest in politics at that stage yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 I used to like to hear me dad talk about them. He
 was a sort of a - he belonged a - can't - not a union, something else belonging to his work. I can't say what it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 But were you interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. Because this man used to come - this Mr - Mr Thornilow was the President and dad used to - sort o
f - tell him the - he was the practical side of it and Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987527\charrsid14039999 Thornilow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 sort of used what dad told him - when he made his report. I can't - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987527\charrsid14039999 it\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 not a union, it's - they have this same thing today but I can't just say it. Trades Council. That's what it was. I've got it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987527\charrsid14039999 
And sometimes this Mr Thornilow would come to our house and there'd be one or two of the men from the workshop when dad was working for his father and they'd sit and discus and - and say what they thought was right and what was wrong and so on. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
And - I was all ears. It interested me, very much so. But - and of course we was all threatened to keep quite and not to speak when me father was speaking or any of these gentleman. We were - we were made to have good manners. We wouldn't be allowed to ta
k
e if your parents were speaking. You'd wait until you - was - got a chance and there's nobody speaking. But I really did like it. 'Cos - when we got into the last form at Huntingdon Street, we had debates. And I - I - loved it. On all sorts of different t
hings and - didn't know anything much about politics but - I used to read the Post and that kind of thing and - yes.
