\insrsid12987527\charrsid14039999 And if there was a - something - on at the - either the Hippodrome or the Empire it was only ninepence in the gods and we'd save up 'til we'd got this ninepence to go. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 'Cos we liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Grace usually. And sometimes John went with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls - at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. I'd got one girl at work I - she used to come
 - sometimes she'd come to tea on a Sunday and I used to go to her house on a Sunday. And - we'd go for walks sometimes on a Sunday. If Grace didn't want to go - perhaps - Grace had other interests you see and she said, I'm not going out now. I'd say, oh 
well I'll go and fetch Florrie Smith then and go with her. And I didn't have a lot of friends. But we went out. And we - the embankment was our - second home. And I used to walk often from there to Atcliffe on Trent and walk back again. We loved it all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you have any special friends at this time, was Florrie Smith special?
