a
nd found out where the Young Woman's Christian Association was. They feared he was blind you see, for me to go and arranged for one of the men to take to the station, that was the kind of man he was. Oh I couldn't - I couldn't praise him sufficiently. And
 - when I got there the sister sent for me and she said, I cannot find you accommodation, most difficult. I said, I haven't asked you to. I said, I'm going to the Christian - the Young }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 Women
\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  Christian Association. I said, I shall find a place. Or if not, 
I said, my - I'm, my boss told me to go to the police station and they're compelled to find me somewhere. And he said it's a - a dock city and - and anyway while - when I did get to see the doctor, they made me wait an awful long while and he - he told me
 then that - it was - he was doing physical instructing while he was getting well to go back to France. These were the new recruits. And of course he was a bit a crazy you know and he was taking them in these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 Nissan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  huts for - punchball. He used to train th
