ful. Never let him bump himself there because it could - and of course he made - it was a tragedy to him, in any case, because it was of his own life. So - I stayed with him 'til he'd got the sight back. And I always remember, I'd had a blue costume to go
 
to a girls wedding in and - I thought I'd put this on this morning. I used to visit him, they used to let me go every day. And - I was coming down the ward, he was propped - I thought he was propped up in bed a bit more. And I heard him say - I can see so
