eorges' sight you see, in the one eye, he'd got no sight of course in the other. And - he was ; very weak because he got depressed. What good am I to anybody, oh I had an awful time with him, I could not - he says - we were going to go with the regiment t
o India, was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 due}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  for the trooping season and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 when}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  - the war was over we'd made all these plans and everything went. No - nothing he could do properly. He was termed as a -
