ent, boxed for the regiment. What shall I do with myself? He was no reader, he looked at a book, no, I don't want to read that. He never read a book through. Although he - he'd got a first class certificate of education in the Army. He wasn't badly - he w
a
s better educated than I really. But - he couldn't - that wasn't his - way. I was very sorry, I always think that made him - erratic, as he was. I can - oh yes, I can understand it. And I must tell you one little incident when I got - I was waiting to fin
d out where I was going to - where this Young }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 Women\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 Christian Association was, one of the men in the bed as I passed up the ward to come out, said, go to that little V.A.D. Hospital across the road, missus, he said, and, he said, they'll find you a bed, not like this lot here, he was going off. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 I said,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14039999  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 all right I understand. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
