ohn says to George one morning, we haven't tried the farms have we. There was a lot of little farms round Nottingham, in the villages and that. So George says, oh we've tried a few things, come on, we might as well try that. Oh - when they come home at ni
g
ht, that day - oh I said, get outside, whatever have - is it. And our John - mother says to John, get upstairs, strip yourself, get the whole lot off, put your best things on. She said, good God it's like a farmyard. He said, so it is, we've been muck spr
e
ading. And they'd got a bag of potatoes. The farmer had given them a bag of apples. Those farmers were wonderful to them lads. But the dirtier the jobs the better - oh, he says, we're cleaning the pigs out. Oh, he says, happen - you think cows smell, you 
wait 'til -
