Yes. Oh yes. But - he couldn't - they weren't experienced farm workers so they couldn't expect to get a proper - you didn't any case - in any case get - good money in those days. But it - they'd alwa
ys give them a bit of something. A few potatoes or a few apples or whatever was going. And they did that for quite a long while 'til he - there was no more of that. And he was all right a long time after that. And then he used to belong to the British Leg
ion. And he was on one of the committees, George was. And - they said they was going to see - there was so much unemployment in Nottingham they was going to see if they could approach some of the big firms. There was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 Adlers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 , Players, Boots and all these peo
ple, if they'd help to get a few of the men, if it was only about temporary to get them started back to work after the war. So, you see George, he could speak fairly well you see, he was educated, and they chose him on the committee. So of course he - he 
l
oved it, it was somewhere to get him out the house, it was a bad life for a man to lead. And - they got a letter form the - the railway asking for their representative to call and they'd like to interview them to see what they had in mind or what kind of 
m
en they wanted them to take on, but they were interested in the scheme. Of course George went. And he came, he sat down in the chair, him, he said, I go - I go, he said, cadging the jobs for the men and I've got the devil myself and I don't want it. It - 
it really was - he was a delegate and he says they offered him - he says, well we've nothing much we can offer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999  you - you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 know, because you can't do any skilled work. He said, it's not me, he said, I'm just the delegate from the region who's seeing what you 
can offer these men. And how many you can take. Oh, can only take one in any case. This man was very curt. What about yourself, he says, you're a bright lad, he said, you can do something can't you? So George said, well I don't know, I've not any trade in
 
my fingers. He was strong you see. But, he said, it's not me, I - I'm just here for - to my - my committee, tell them. Oh no, you're not any more. And they talked him out of it. I said, well never mind dear, you've done a bit towards it. Yes, but George s
aid, you wanted it for the - they're worse off than we are. I said, well I can't do anything about it. And it was - unloading big planks of wood from the railway as it came in and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 stacking}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  it in this yard. Oh it was heavy and he used to come home really exh
austed and ; that. And he didn't stick it - I knew - I wouldn't - he knew he wouldn't stick it 'cos he was against it in the first place. I don't think he was there - three months at the outside. He said, well I've got me cards. He didn't - I said, well t
hat's a bit of all right, what are you going to do for the wages then? I said, what did you do? Sell, he said - they caught me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 smoking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 . I said, I expected that you wouldn't leave your smoking alone would you? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 But - it was out of work a long, long while again. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh he went to a printing firm - Round Street, wanted a man - a man to do odd jobs. Stack boxes in racks and - all sorts of things like that. For - that wasn't much money at all but anyway I thought it was better than him hanging about. And - he went for
 a while but - I new from the beginning he wasn't going to like it. But he didn't want to do the exact work and he - he'd got the place reorganised and every - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6301576\charrsid14039999  fact}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 he organised himself out of it pretty quick. I knew he would do, I told him, I said, you
 have to - when you do a job for a firm George, you have to do it their way, not your way. He - he was very one for saying, you shouldn't do that like that - even to me about the housework. Of course I got used to it and never listened, I just ignored it.
 
It wasn't any good going on about it, it was just his way. You see, and I knew, I said - acting a fool, I said, you'll lose the job. And he did. And then he never did anything for - a long spell, I can't tell how long. Oh and I - in those days you could o
n
ly have so much dole and then a period and then you had to wait so much longer before you could come on it again, you see, there was no money or anything and this gentleman came to to door and said, where was - was Mr Williams in? And of course I can kick
