w
 for you Annie because you'll have to - your husband will have to get them. But of course he didn't because he was only a night watchman. So it was - I think it was me young brother. He says, why don't you join the Forresters? I said, what's that? Sick an
d holiday he said. They charge you a penny for the youngest child, tuppence a week for the next one, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 three pence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 for the next one and fourpence for the tops, that'd be four and one three's seven, two's nine, that was tenpence a week for four children. And t
hat covered you, you got - the choice of four doctors and all medicines and everything free. And I was in that for years. And then of course then they started the new - beginning to get ready for the new health insurance that went out, but you see, I paid
 
bills. Old Doctor Clark very - this one is now, he's not any relation to my Doctor Clark but he was - he was there before him, it was his practice. And I - I'd - he died about a fortnight now I think I heard - I owed him another shilling or something and 
I went to take it and I didn't even know he'd died. We used to take it as we'd got it, you see, but he said, I never mind as long as you do pay me. But we - he had to have this, we'd no other choice you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Looking back do you think you should have seen a doctor when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh definitely. Oh yes. I'd have been sent away to a convalescent town. Definite. 'Cos - each one of them when they did see me, how long have you been like this child? All the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did they recommend treatment you couldn't have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh very often, yes. I know one - one said, she want's building up, to me mother. It was very expensive. It's The juice of the meat or something. And he said, that's what you want Annie. He said, I shall have to see that - if you ca
n't get some. So I said, how much is it? I think how much is it was engrained in my head. So he said, oh it's very expensive child, he said. I'll have to ask my mother. And she asked someone else. Oh - a little tiny jar like that was - pounds. Oh no, I co
u
ldn't have had that. But - they used to get one part of the town, I never did, but my children had, Bio from school and emulsion for their chests. From the schools. You got - if the teacher heard a child coughing; in school they'd say, you all at the head
mistress's office before you go home and you'd have to pay a few coppers for it but it wasn't anything like what it was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You don't remember the name of the doctors at the dispensary do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Not at the dispensary I don't, there was - you see - n
o, I'll tell you what - where there might be one - where - this - there was four there, I do remember in - there was a big - yes, the big doctor, we called him the big doctor because he was such a big man, Doctor Diemer and there was a Doctor Sheppard and
 then - who - and then the little one. But I liked them all. They all worked in this for this sick and annual club where we paid fourpence a week as you might say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 So you didn't feel you were getting a less good doctor than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Gracious m
e no. We had the best of attention. When Georgie had jaundice once, I never seen it before of course and I'd no idea what it was but I knew it was something serious and when he came and he said - this - it was the big Doctor Diemer He said, no food whatso
ever but - pure milk from the cow. I said - he said - well - what milk do you have? Well, I said, I have the stores milk. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 Sterilized}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  milk or - and they even arranged these little Moss's farm somewhere out at Woodthorpe, and they arranged for that milk to be
 brought to me so it shouldn't have been tampered with in any way. Because George had - he was only a little lad. Be about five or six. To live on. During that time. Oh they - they - no stone unturned for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Could you tell me your children's birthdays, Joyce was 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. Yes, Joyce was born in - Joyce was born in 1919. On the seventeenth of June
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 The second was the very end of 1922?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. December the thirty - December 31st - New Year's Eve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 And then Eric?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 George.
 He's the eldest boy. 28th of October - now this is where I always go wrong - there was about three and a half years between him and Grace. So that would be? Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 That would be 1926?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. Yes, that's right. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 And Eric was born - not quite tw
o years, I had him very, very quick after George, on the 19th of August - under two years.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Could you tell me the jobs they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How did you manage the housekeeping in those years before 1919, you were living with your mother weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, the first four years of our married life I lived in two rooms at their house. So that would be from 1917 to - '21. '22 perhaps.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you know what your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well he wasn't working, he did - he never - he was four years co
mpletely without work. All he got was his - the pension for the loss of his eye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did he give it all to you and you coped with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well of course he - he was a bit fussy about this, it was his eye and he resented having to give me anything really
. But I pointed out to him that you must give me something, I can't do it all. And then I'd give him so much }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
, for his cigarettes and so on. And - of course before the week was out he was always broke, you know what men are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You had two rooms with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, I had two rooms with mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you do the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh yes, I did - did all of it. And I kept mother's part clean because she wasn't very - she was getting old you know and I did her washing too and blackleaded the grat
e and that kind of thing, as I'd always done, it was no hard - you know, nothing any different to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Were you making clothes or mending them yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh - made all the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 s things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You hadn't got any children before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh no, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 before}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 I got - I had - well I made - I prepared for the babies coming. Made all their layouts and crocheted matinee coats and bonnets and everything and so on - I - I've always liked sewing. But of course I went to work as long as ever I could before Jo
yce was born. Went 'til after - end of January and she was born - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
nd of June. But you see I was in the order room and when I began to show the - it made me feel uncomfortable, you see, I said I'd have some work at home, and I did some of the work f
or them at home for a while. Then it - it was a bad spell come along, so it was seasonable this kind of work, home work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When your husband was at home did he help with jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, he was very good about that. He - well, you see, I was - it was the cellar kitchen house, you remember me explaining to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Which rooms did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
We had the two front rooms, the front living room, that was on level with the front street, and the bed - - bedroom above. But we'd got to go down a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 flight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 of stairs into mother's living room and the scullery was off there. So every drop of water had to be carried up in buckets. And all our slops taken down and we had coal fires and what kind of thing. Well George always would fill the coal bucket i
n the morning and he'd bring me up a couple of buckets of cold water to start off. He was very good in that, and he would - he didn't like going errands, he loathed going an errand, but he would do other things. About - he's done the ironing for me, if I'
ve had a rush of work in - you know, and I was aching to get it done he'd just say, oh well, I'll do the ironing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Would he ever do washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh he has done on occasions but not very often. At that stage, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, he would - he could always cook himself a meal and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Cleaning of your rooms at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 He kept - he liked anything that wanted polishing. But he didn't want - he didn't care for anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you do decorating at all there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, well I'd nev
er done any before but of course we couldn't afford to pay a man so he says, I'm sure if I tried I could do it. And in the end he was doing he papering and I was doing the pasting and handing him the stuff and we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 them quite nice, 'cos you could get the paper rather cheaply you see and made we could keep the place nice - quite reasonable.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How did you cope about meals, where did you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh we had - my - I had me own private living room you see, that was the front room of mother's 
house you see, so everything had to be carried up the stairs again and down, cook it and I used to have a big tray and over it over to bring it up to keep it nice and hot and if he was in the house and not doing anything he would carry the hot food up you
 see. He was very good in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You cooked downstairs, did you say you had gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. It was a gas stove in that - back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Would you have had breakfast there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes, well we lived completely alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What did you usually have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Well we - I used to - one time it was a craze to give all the - the children porridge, I loathed it but - and George liked it, so I used to give them porridge and a bit of bread and butter to fill up. And on a Sunday we
 made a special treat, we had - if we could - if it was possible we had either egg and bacon or something like that. That was a treat for Sunday but never in the week. I couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What sort of midday meals were you having at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes
, well - I carried on from the normal way that we usually got on you know. Tried to give him a green vegetables most days and made them soups and broths and rice puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When it was just the two of you did you do it the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes. Yes. I baked my own bread. I did that - oh I did that for years, I always used to bake a little batch for mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Who taught you how to bake bread because your mother didn't did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. She - no, oh she wouldn't let you touch the food. Well - the latter
 - latter years at school we had the cookery class and - mind you I forgot it all by then, I thought to myself, I'm not going to let this beat me, and a friend of mine, she said, I'll give you a rough idea if you're a bit - you know, if you're not quite s
u
re. I said, well I'm not quite sure of myself about it. Because she said it was so much cheaper. And of course I watched her one day and when I saw how she did it and the things she used I'd got it then, I was all right, and from then - oh for years after
 
- I didn't give it up until the beggars - as fast as I made a batch which ought to have lasted half the week - we'll have it while it's hot man, it's lovely. You can well imagine it can't you. I said, I can't keep pace with this, I can't bake every day, t
wice a week is enough. So I gave it up after then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When there was just the two of you did you make jam yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No, we never did anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Wine or beer or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you learn to make medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh I just - I just - oh I'll ask our mum. You sort of - when she's there you know
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 As that stage did you have your main meal in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What would you have had in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well we never had anythi
ng very much except for tea it was bread and butter, a bit of jam for the children, or anything like that. And - for supper - I'd give them a bit of cheese if I could. But the kiddies didn't very rare - rarely have anything. Just a drop - a cup of cocoa, 
they liked cocoa - George liked cocoa tool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When it was just the two of you did you have anything different on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well I always - always tried to make a decent tea. He liked a bit of cake and things like that for his tea and usually it was 
eggs and bacon if I could and of course if we hadn't got the money for it we just had some toast or something. We managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Where did you get your vegetables from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh I had to buy them all from the shop. There was a little back garden but - oh you'd put - you could put it in half of this room.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you used to go to market for vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh I used to go down the covered market. They were cheaper than anywhere else but - I don't think we got this one greengrocery and they were very good and mostly very fresh. We were apt to stop there once you'd got satisfaction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Once they knew you I expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, I suppose so. And they were very fresh, we were very fortunate in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you never have tinned or dried vegetables in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. Never tinned vegetables ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well I'd some - if I'd got a few shillings left I'd buy them some apples or an orange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You hadn't any hens or anything in the back yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh no. It was forbidden you see, there were too - the houses were too closely packed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How many times a week did you eat meat when there was just your husband and you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well - if I could I got a little joint for Sunday which we always washed up for Monday. And then we'd probably hav
e - a leg of - a leg of beef and - kidney stew for the next day. Most days - oh and we'd have sausage one day, it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 depended}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 how the money ran out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You could manage meat most days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes, we mostly did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Tinned eat ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever get extra meat like your mother did the rabbits and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh occasionally we did, yes, but that was in place of anything else. That was a luxury. If this man came - we knew he was a poacher - and he'd come to the door sometimes with this cou
ple of rabbits and - give me so and so for them. We got them for next to nothing, else we couldn't have had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever have to go short so your husband could have things in food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well I did but I mean I'd sort of try to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 camaflage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  it - I
 didn't want to make them feel embarrassed if they thought I wasn't having any. Then I said, would you like a bit more bread? And one of them would say - he'd say - George would say, well I haven't seen you have any. Oh I'm not hungry. 'Cos I didn't - I -
 no I didn't go really hungry you know, just having a little bit, but there was no - no real variety in it. You see, I couldn't always have - afford a second vegetable, 'cos they were very expensive. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 greens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What did you do on Bank Holidays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh yes, if it was a nice day we'd take - well this is - before the children came - we always used to like to go for a walk down - the embankment or go and have a walk on Clifton Grove, we loved that. But that was - there was trams of cou
rse and we did go on the tram. And we've often walked back. Because if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 was a nice day. We couldn't when we'd got the children you see and the prams and that kind of thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 So they'd have to be satisfied with the Hoverington or the Forest. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 But we enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Between your marriage and the end of 1919 did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You hadn't any relations or anyone you could stay with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh, I'd only got the one bedroom you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Can you remember anything you did with your husband - on Christmas Day that was different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
No, it was always - we'd always kept Christmas Day the same, he sort of fell in with the family, he was treated as one of the family from mother - they'd all known him from a boy of about fifteen and he 
just sort of followed on - we didn't do anything very special but - if it was possible - we couldn't afford a fowl or anything like that but we did have a rabbit or a bit of pork and had a nice dinner. Never bothered about any tea much. And then in the ev
ening the married sisters would come down and that and we'd all get together and have a talk and we enjoyed our Christmas that way. There was no television or tele - whatsname, but we were quite happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 At that stage were there any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Yes. There was - John used to play the mouth organ. He was very musical but - poor lad he had to - well it didn't matter how cold it was he had to go in the attic to play it, she couldn't bear it. Even at that stage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you sort of have sing-songs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Yes, we all used to - yes, we all knew - there were certain old songs that we all seemed to know. Songs often that mother had sung to us. And I always remember we used to say it was the only year father ever - only time father ever 
sang, and I used to say - go on dad, sing us your song, it's Christmas. I never forgot it. Poor Old Joe. And he used to put the actions to it, he - he had us all in fits with laughing. Poor Old Joe has gone to rest - I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 sat down}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  by my Mary's side and a stor
y she did tell, was about old - no, Darkie Jess. It was about old Darkie Jeff. 'Cos I used to get the words all mixed up, it was a long while before I could right until he was ever so old, he was - it was not himself if he wouldn't sing it. But we had to 
d
o a lot of coaxing you know. But - I - we did love it, and all the sisters knew - they knew all the songs that mother used to sing. She was a great one for singing to us and we all loved it. All old fashioned songs, and that kind of thing. And then we all
 sang the songs we knew from school. My older sisters - we often learnt the same songs after I went to school that they knew and say, oh I know that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Were there books in your part of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well only.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You said you had them when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Yes, we had to do. But - well - she didn't bother then so much. And I did go to I got going to the library quite a bit, there was a free library near us, and I did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 enjoy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  it but I had so little time that I had to sort of sneak a few minut
es and that then I got - disheartened because if I got entranced in a book and I didn't want to leave it and I know all the things that were waiting for me to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you take newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Dad had the Post.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Wel
l dad always used to pass it on to George you see and we had - I think on a Sunday - he had a paper on Sunday, can't just remember what it was. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Magazines at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did your husband have any difficulty reading with the one eye?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh no, he used to tell me he could see twice as much as I could see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever read aloud together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. I always used to like to get all me cleaning done by Sa
turday dinner so the place was all nice and spick and span for Sunday and we'd have a bit of rest, say - Saturday afternoon, then George says, let's got and have a walk down the market. And it was the covered in market then, the old exchange - and we'd ju
s
t walks about the stalls and have a look round, see if there was anything we could afford to buy and we were quite satisfied at that. But George liked to play billiards and there was a billiards room nearby and if - if I didn't feel like going, I didn't g
o
 ever, but he used to go sometimes and we'd come back, we weren't late, and he'd say, I'm going down to the billiard hall for a bit, and I said, all right. But that was - an odd times we went to the pictures but - he wasn't too keen on pictures. He was li
ke me, he liked the theatre better. But that was an event, you see, it's got to be something special, or something special we wanted to see that we could arrange it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How did you spend Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Sundays, well we always had a lay}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 in. Sunday was the day we hadn't got to work by the clock. But - very little different to any other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you put on different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well we had - you'd got to keep one thing decent you see, we couldn't - I would never work in the dress t
hat I - Sunday dress like. Well we hadn't any others to do it with so you just couldn't do it until you could get better clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When you were first married did you think it was wrong to work or enjoy yourself on a Sunday or did you think it didn't matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh - well, we had to be very discreet. We couldn't be noisy at all, if George - sometimes he would act the clown you know, and I used to say, oh don't make a noise, you'll disturb mum. Oh dear. Yes she was down below and - but the sound did - 
it always seemed to - she could hear it more. I know if we were laughing a lot she'd say, it's not any hope - hope of me getting a rest Sunday afternoon when you two's on giggling. You see, we used to get into trouble a bit for it. But she didn't - not re
ally cross you know but she liked us to have been - or we've gone a walk. I've taken them - when the kiddies were very little I used to say, well I'll take them round on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 field}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  a bit, it's a long day if you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 don\rquote t.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
. You see, and I've worked - I've done wo
rk at home when I've had it many a time, if I'd got to finish some for Monday and I hadn't got it done, he's say, well I'm going out round for a bit and - and I'd sit and work when the children were in bed. I'd sooner do it than be late with the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 ork if it was promised you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You felt quite happy about this, you weren't made to feel guilty about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh no. Well it was the life of most of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When you were little you weren't allowed to do anything on Sunday were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Nothing whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When did you begin changing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Well as we - when we started going out to work and we knew what other girls did. One of - one of the girls said, oh I did so and so on Sunday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 
And I - I just said - and if you could ask a girl to - one of your gi
rlfriends you worked with - I - to tea on Sunday, mother never provided any tea, it was just the same bread and butter and this lovely jam and - I said to her once, could I bring Florrie Smith to have a cup of tea with us? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 I said, you know, she did ask me the other week, mum, I went. She said, yes, I know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 And it was a long, long time before she made up her mind. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 But she says, you'll do everything yourself because I'm going to have my rest. And instead of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 lying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  on the sofa which she did, the old sofa, when 
I brought the girl to tea she went and laid on the bed, you see. But - not very often. I - we - you didn't ask very often, well I knew how the situation was, and we knew that she could ill afford it and I thought well if she's - she's worked hard at that 
chebonning all week she must be tired. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When you were first married did you attend a place as worship or not on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. I'm ashamed to say it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 So you don't know anything about church activities at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh I used to have the magazine. They used to send it to me from the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you belong to any clubs organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. We never said grace at meals, not ever. In our own youth and - I never - oh, well - 
I say no - I always liked them to say when - if they finished first - and I wouldn't let them leave the table and start running about if I'd not - say your manners and get down, and say thank you for - what did I say, thank you for my good dinner. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 Thank you for my good dinner, please may I leave the table? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
That was - well it was a form of grace. But nothing else - nothing religious attached to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When you were first married did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 take}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  an interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, I used to like to - me dad u
sed to belong to some - well he never went to the meetings but he always used to talk about them - the Conservatives and - I used to like to listen to him talking about them. But I took no - personal interest in it, not until after we were married. And th
e
n the - I - had a friend whose father-in-law stood for the council, he lived opposite me, he was a Labour member and I - I let them have the room once for the con - for a - committee meeting. And I did go to those meetings if mother would listen to the ch
ildren. You see. And - I - I got very interested in the Women's Association at one time and I - I was president of it for a little while but - then I was ill and I couldn't keep it up so I had to give up again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 So you were more inclined to the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Why did you think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Well I think it was - being on the edge of - you know - sort of - having to work for every ha'penny and not knowing where the next is coming from and they had a - they had a way of looking - a sho
pkeeper was looked down on as if he was dirt you know, and I used to - there was the butcher, he was a rank Conservative and he used to get my blood right up. I once heard him say, the devils don't want to work. He was talking about some people who - hadn
'
t got any work and I knew they'd tried every so hard and - I thought to myself, you're darned lucky to have a shop to work in. And I felt resentful. All the time about - I always have and I still do. I said, you want all the privileges but a man whose got
 to work for - doesn't have - it wasn't a thing that they carry on with, perhaps be going on nicely for a few weeks, stop this now, no more work - and was out of work. And there was no - only periods of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 dole}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  in those days. You couldn't get any assistance - there was no - no public assistance or anything like that, you just had to manage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did your husband take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. Used to go to the meetings with me sometimes because, you see, we were friendly with this family, they lived op
posite me and we were quite friendly with them, and they said, come along, come to the meeting. And I - I really enjoyed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 But he really wasn't interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What were his views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well I think the billiard hall was his - I thi
nk the billiard hall was - and he liked football, if he could get enough money to go to a football match he was happy. He did - you know, he'd listen to them and he'd talk to them but he - and he belonged the British Legion.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you vote in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 And you voted Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  yes. I never voted anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 I never asked him 'cos I said it was personal, and I believed he did because he seemed to - he - sort of - with us knowing th
is family and knowing the ins and outs and that I believe he - he felt the same as I did. Yes, yes, I never knew for sure, I couldn't say for a certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you have political discussions with your parents because they were Conservative weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Well they were at the time but - after a while dad seemed to be - I - something happened, I don't know what it was - something that - about the worker - dad said, they'd cut your throat, they would, they wouldn't let you work. Oh I know. Now when w
ould this be, I can't remember - when the miners were - they wouldn't give them any work, they turned them away from the pits. That was after mother went in that little house and it so infuriated me father because - he - he - he thought that - well - as I
 do today, to think of a man having to go into the bowls of the earth to me they must heroes every one of them. And dad was so inflamed at the way they treated these men. They got practically - they were practically }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 starving.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  I can't remember the - it was s
omething to do with the - wasn't a strike - they turned them away, they wouldn't give them the work. Then there was a lot of miners round there where we lived. And from then on - father wouldn't hear of the Conservatives, he says -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you or your hus
band ever feel under any pressure from anyone to vote for a particular party? Were your employers interested in who you voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh no, well they - oh yes, a canvasser would come round but - most of them we knew if they were in the party and from g
oing to these meetings and with these friends of ours being - oh, they'd say, oh it's all right here. That's all that would be said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Just that short time. When I went - and I went - I used to go about once
 a week. And odd times they'd run a little whist drive at one of the schools and if George would stop and look after the kiddies I would go there. Only about sixpence I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you take part in any other political activity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. Just for these - this little group that we knew you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Because you knew them really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes? They were working people the same as ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When you weren't working how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
I never seemed to - if I - if I couldn't get any work to earn money with I'd be doing something - making the kids frocks or something, knitting the socks and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You occasionally went to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes, this was
 - it would be some special thing. If we read in the Post there was so and so on at the theatre Royal, and we got our knowledge of that with - my sisters used to be big - big - the elder ones were big theatre goers and we used to buy a magazine giving you
 
the pictures out of the play and the musical - so I knew all this thing. And when they'd done with this you see, oh you like this don't you? And there'd be captions under the pictures you know and telling you what it was and this will be coming to the the
atre }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 Royal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
 in such and such a time. I said, oh yes, oh I shall have to see if I can save up sixpence and then I'll be able to go. You know, and we looked forward to it. And George liked that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How often would this be, sort of once a month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh not as - not as - not as much as once a month. Just depended what it was that was there at the time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 What did you specially like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh musical comedies. And a lot of the straight plays. The Arcadians and The Country girl and - what was the - a
ll those musical comedies, and I went - there was one man I liked - I went to see - who was that man, The Only Way, Martin Harvey. Oh I thought that was wonderful. And I saw - the magazine - in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 Chinese}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  Bungalow and there was a - and I saw one just called the C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 ruel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  Sea, and I never forgot that. I can't even remember the name - it was a straight play, just talking but I thought it was wonderful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever go out together in the evening or anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, odd times. If - if mother and da
d would say, well - we'll - if you and George want to go out for an hour we'll listen the children but I couldn't trust mother because she had them a bit she'd have them all out of bed. You see. And it was more trouble to me when I came back and they were
 all upset and excited you see so - I wouldn't go - not very often, but odd times me sister }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 Alice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
, the one that had got the - and her husband, they liked a game of cards. I loved playing whist, George did too. And we'd go to their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  perhaps one Sunday and then when the children were all in bed, or if they weren't in bed - let the bigger ones look at their picture book or something and mother'd say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Might you have done this before you had children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh we used to go to Alice's quite a bit, yes. We played cards but only Sunday night, perhaps for a couple of hours. But we did like it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did your husband ever go out without you from the very beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes, he was a - yes, he used to go into the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 square}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  - there used to be a - a man selli
ng newspapers down there and George knew him. And George said, I'll go down in the - in the square for a paper, he'd be gone hours. And - oh my, crikey, you've been a long while. Oh, he said, we got talking about - he'd been in the Army with George, all t
h
is kind of thing. If ever he met anybody that had - it was like going home to him you see. And he used to go and - and he loved that billiard room. I used to be a bit cross about that sometimes. But it was on our road you see, it wasn't far. I knew where 
he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did he ever go to clubs, institutes or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Just to the - odd time he'd go in the pub - very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 rarely}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  though. But he was in the British Legion and he had to go to the meeting once a week or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever go to any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 pubs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  or institutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Would you have been able to go into a pub or were they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1334943\charrsid14039999 men\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Oh no, you could go in. I used to go in the pub every night to fetch mum and dad's supper beer you see. You could - oh there was no restriction, the men and women all went together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever go in for a drink?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Yes. I had - on several occasions. When - me brother-in-law, Harold, when he won that - some money on the pools - they came and asked us to go, take us out, they took us in the Talbot, I'd never been in there before. And I did really enjoy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you and your husband ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Odd time. Out it was very rarely. Because you see - he - I had a drink - the money for a drink with him but if it comes to two he'd got to go short so I used to - go on then George, if you want to go and have a drink you go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When you were first married to did you belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes. Yes. When - when Mr Redgate gave me that - gave us that bonus, when the men were cal
led up to go and he have us two pound a month which was wealth to us I was in the ten pound money society in Heathcote Street and I - I was on - I kept that up - it wasn't until I really couldn't afford the shilling a week that I had to let it drop.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you belong to a boot club at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 That was the one my mother had. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You weren't in a sick club at that stage were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Not until the children - you know - got to be about two or three or so then we paid tuppence or threepence a week into the sick - club.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Any funeral club or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
No. We always - mother used to say, when you get married and before you have a family, the best thing is to take out an insurance - on - as the children come along. And I used
 to pay threepence for George, tuppence for me and a penny for Joyce and then have the penny then. I didn't want to pay a shilling a week all the time. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you or your husband take part in any sport when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 first}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you go to concerts ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No, we none of us seemed to go to concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Occasionally, just as I say an odd occasion. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did either of you bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh George loved it. I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 This was horses was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did either of you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
I can't remember if we - he loved the paper, I used to say I don't know what he'd find to interest him - seemed as if he read every - every line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You didn't keep any pets at that stage did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Yes. He once - somebody had bread some goldfinches and he - I don't know what it was he'd done for this man but this man gave him one. And mother had got an old cage and - oh he polished every wire on that cage. And he - that
 bird was beautiful, we had him years. And he sang lovely. And then years after I did have a dog and I had a cat and I've been very fond of both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 But not at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you have any other interests outside the home at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No, I can't - well we never really had time you see, if it comes to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever go out yourself and enjoy yourself on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Odd occasions. There was just - this little whist drive and dance, it was called. Belong - the - got up by
 the Labour party. George wouldn't always go. He'd say, oh I'll - I'll sooner go in the billiard hall. You see, so I - then I have gone - it was only for about a couple of hours on a Saturday evening. Didn't go always. But it just depended what I'd got to
 do. And - I really and truly enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Nobody outside the home helped you in your domestic life at that stage did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well - this - Alice, this one - the Naval man's wife - my sister - she was awfully good to us. But it was in such a - she w
ouldn't let you think she was helping. I've got this and we can't finish it, would you and the children finish it, and sort of things like that. And I know when George was going after a job, his shirt, I'd patched it up and it was so shabby and I - I happ
ened to say, you know, I wish I could have got him a new shirt to go in, he might have got the job. But nothing was said, but presently one of Alice's children brought this parcel to me. There was a little note on top, this is an old one of }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4399113\charrsid14039999 Harold\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 , perhaps it'll be a bit smarter than George's. Things like that. She was the only one who did anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 And she did it very tactfully?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh - oh yes, nobody knew. The child didn't even know what the parcel contained you see. And when I tried to thank he
r afterward, oh, she said, forget it. That was all you could get out of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 If you were confined to bed at this period how did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well there again George was awfully good. He seemed - he did - very well for a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You had lots of relatives living round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes. There was quite a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Well - it used to be - a usual thing or me sisters and that when they've been doing the shopping - it was on the main road then, we'll call in our mum's, you
 see, sometimes there'd be two or three of them down - when I got downstairs with a bucket or something, there was two or three of them called in to see mum and they would all have a little chat and then mostly at the weekends one or two of them would com
e in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you have any friends who weren't relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Where did you see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Well this was this - who lived straight opposite - this - in this - they were - her father-in-law was the councilor, and she liked - she w
ould like me - she liked freedom, and that's where we were good friends because we often go to the library together and I was - she was more - the only friend I had for years. But I used to sometimes see the girls I'd worked with - on odd occasions.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 The friend opposite - you went to her house and she came to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you and your husband share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh he was very friendly with the Thundercli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4399113\charrsid14039999 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 fs. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did he have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, there was tw
o men who were in the same Regiment as George who were Nottingham men and - when - after the war and they were discharged and we were living in mother's rooms and - it was quite by surprise - a knock came at the door one Sunday and I went and there this m
a
n stood in uniform. Well I didn't know him. He was older you see, he was a - me brothers generation you see but of course he knew George. And he said, is Williams in? So George said, I know - I told you, the door opened straight into the room - I know tha
t
 voice. Well he came to me, he said, why it's Darkie Stevenson. Well after all these years. They were old chums. Oh he came in and for quite a long while - he used to go down there and they came to us. And he was a - working at the Clifton pit and he got 
George in the Clifton colliery }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4399113\charrsid14039999 band}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
. Couldn't get him a job at the pit but he got him in the band. And he really enjoyed his life a bit better from then. It - it was something that he liked you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 These friends you invited to the house, how often did they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh - not very often. Perhaps once or two or three a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes, I'd make a cup of tea and - I'd usually - with baking me own bread and usually got some cakes and bits of things 
and they'd be passed round. But never - we wouldn't - we didn't have what was called a sit down meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you invite them in on particular days or occasions or just because you felt like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes, just because - yes - because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Not because it was a holiday or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Was it usually a Sunday or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh it was - sometimes they'd pop in on Sunday because they knew we weren't working on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Would you say the friends invited were your friends or your husband's friends or friends you shared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well they were all - they were all really three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. Very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did neighbours call in casually in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes, they were your
 friends - and they probably wouldn't stay, they'd just a call in, have a chat and say, oh well be seeing you. Oh - come round so and so, they might say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you often go to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 I went more to me own sisters, you see, I'
d got so many of them. But I - I was always - I was very often with Sarah, and then this other girl from work, I went to her place quite a few times. But after they'd all got married I lost track of them and I didn't like them to know that I was hard up y
ou see, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
People often tell us that in those days people made their own amusements, what did you do when you got together with friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Well it was mostly talking and a sing song and a game of cards with - and - and they did
n't play dominoes, they played the dominoes in the pubs but - dad loved a game of cards. And we'd all sit -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Was it whist mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Whist or - there was - more games than whist but - we girls all liked them to play whist because it was more interes
ting, but there was one game that me dad liked because everybody could take part. I can't think it was now. We played it for ha'pennies. Can't think of it for the world but I know they used to say if one or two or them had come, come on dad, get the cards
 out. Let's have a game of cards. And I think that was his one amusement really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 You had a struggle to make ends meet at that time, what did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 I used to get a bit fed up sometimes. I - I thought to myself, oh well - but you see,
 there was always this - in - in your mind, that we were all in the same boat round about us. Mother said, that' poor man's been out of work two years, and I never said anything, and I - when I was going upstairs I was chortling to myself, I said, and yes
, and you've been out nearly three years now but she wasn't - he wasn't a poor man you see, cos his wife worked. And it made me laugh afterwards. I thought - well - but it was so young. It was very general after that 1914 war. The poverty was dreadful.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 To begin with your husband wasn't working so you knew this from the very end of the war didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
Yes, yes. He came out - was it 1922. Was he discharged, something like that. And for the first four years he was home. He never earned a penny. They 
- they - they gave him - I think it was a period of dole, but after that period ran to you'd got to go to work again for so many - months to get the stamps back }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4399113\charrsid14039999 before}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999  you could get any more if you couldn't get work. But you see if he never went to work he never got the stamps and you didn't get any.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Did you ever get help from the guardians or the parish or a charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No. I didn't. But while I was carrying - after I left work when I was carrying Joyce, well the soldiers pay was twelve shillings 
a week you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4399113\charrsid14039999 
Well I was - I got a bit of money by me, I'd been careful with what I'd got, well then I'd got to prepare for her coming and it was Mr Thornicliffe who told me, he says, you know you should get a bit more Annie, I don't know how you're mana
ging to live on that, and I'd got to pay mother for everything and coal and all the lot, I'd got those rooms. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 
And - he gave me some address to go to. Somewhere on Castlegate if I remember correctly. And they - I had to tell this man - you know - my husband
 was a regular soldier and - that, and I was - and he had to pay - they took so much out of his pay with this twelve shillings and he said, you've no other money? I said, no, that's - I can't go to work, not until after this, I said, when baby's - when I'
v
e got the baby, I said, I'll perhaps be able to get some work. And things were bad then. I couldn't get the work to do at home and they made me - I always remember what they. Put it on the paper - a child is - you see, 'cos I hadn't got the baby then but 
the - five - shillings a week until Joyce was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 This was from the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 No, I don't think it was from the Army. Oh it must have been, of course it must.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 They did make up the Army pay didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Yes. You just got the twelve - if y
ou were married - when you were first married and there were just the two of you he had to put so much out of his money and the - you got twelve shillings a week, that was what you - I always - I got that right until Joyce was born. And then - it - it was
 seventeen and six you see. But this - this five shillings did help me. It must have been from the Army. Of course it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 When did your husband actually get discharged from the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 I think it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 1922}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 . Let's see, Joyce was born in 1919 and it'
s - must have been 1922, as near as I can remember. I gave George all his - his discharge papers and his rule book and anything, he set great store by them, and his medals. He thought a great deal of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8407077 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 At that stage did you ever know anyone who was getting help from the Guardians?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15820647 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16006220\charrsid14039999 Oh yes, it was quite - we used to - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15994928\charrsid14039999 have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
